\section{Proof of the result}\label{section3}

We now turn to the proof of our result. The physical mass of a Kerr-Newman or Kerr-Newman-AdS black hole is completely determined by its horizon area $A$, angular momentum $J$ and electric charge $Q$ through a Smarr formula

text:
\begin{align}
dM_{\text{ext}} & = \left(\frac{\partial M}{\partial A} \frac{\partial A_{\text{ext}}}{\partial J} + \frac{\partial M}{\partial J}\right) dJ + \left(\frac{\partial M}{\partial A} \frac{\partial A_{\text{ext}}}{\partial Q} + \frac{\partial M}{\partial Q}\right) dQ \nonumber \\
& = \left(\frac{\kappa}{8 \pi} \frac{\partial A_{\text{ext}}}{\partial J} + \Omega \right) dJ + \left(\frac{\kappa}{8 \pi} \frac{\partial A_{\text{ext}}}{\partial Q} + \Phi\right) dQ \nonumber \\
& = \Omega dJ + \Phi dQ, \label{dMext}
\end{align}

nexttext:
In other words, the final mass is above the mass of an extremal black hole with the same angular momentum and electric charge, meaning that the final object is not a naked singularity, that is, the black hole has not been destroyed.




\section{Discussion}

In this paper we proved that an extremal Kerr-Newman or Kerr-Newman-anti de Sitter black hole cannot be destroyed by interacting with (possibly charged) test fields satisfying the null energy condition at the event horizon. It is interesting to note that if the null energy condition is not satisfied then the weak cosmic censorship conjecture may indeed be violated, as shown in~\cite{Duztas15, Toth15} for Dirac fields. 

Our proof can readily be generalized for other black holes satisfying \eqref{second}, \eqref{one} and \eqref{two}, including black holes in higher dimensions. The case of test particles can also be seen as a limit case of our statement, inasmuch as a particle can be seen as a singular limit of a continuous medium \cite{GJ75, LGATN14}.




